                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/6–2840: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scott</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-28T12:00:00-04:30"
                            >June 28, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>94. After successful completion his mission Captain Canaga left by plane today,
                    due to arrive Washington June 30 morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scott</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
